            <p>
                <m>\textbf{Key Takeaway}</m>

            </p>
            <p>
                <ul>
                   
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            A regular pentagon has equal sides and angles. Its area can be found using the formula:
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <me>
                                \text{Area} = \frac{1}{2} \times \text{Perimeter} \times \text{Apothem}
                            </me>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Where <m>p\text{Perimete}= \text{Length} \times 5</m> 
                            and <m>\textbf{Apothem }</m>is the distance from the center of a regular polygon to aside. 
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
